---
Serpentine humanoids of the Saltglass Reach, the Kethari are witnesses to the desert's
deep history. Their water-memories of the Deepwell Confluence predate the Keeper surveys
and exceed anything human instrumentation can produce; their Aquifer Covenant, maintained
as oral tradition and verified at coil-gatherings, has governed eastern water rights
longer than any human institution has existed. Patient beyond the measure of other
peoples, the Kethari have watched civilizations rise and collapse across timescales that
make institutional permanence look like a brief disturbance on the surface of much deeper
time. They continue accumulating the record of what passes before them, and they remember
which institutions received their knowledge and failed to credit it.
